						               													<description>This is a game created for the 18 Microgame Contest!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players: 1&amp;#10;Ages 13+&amp;#10;Time: 15-20 Minutes&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Attack on Omaha Beach follows a squad of American soldiers landing on Omaha Beach June 6th 1944! Your goal is to move up the beach avoiding obstacles and mines, to eventually get to the Pillbox and destroy it!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game consists of phases and turns. You have a demolition engineer and a sniper to help you reach the pillbox.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You must use your Demo Engineer to destroy barriers in your way but don't use all your 6 demo charges or you won't be able to destroy the pillbox and you will lose!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The sniper can help remove German machine gun nests that will attack you while in the open. Your sniper only has 6 shots so make them count, after that you will be shot every time you move in the open or side to side without sight restrictions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You will lay out a 3x3 grid of Beach Terrain card to create the beach assault and as you progress up the beach you will create a new beach assault 3 more times until you get to the pillbox.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Here is the link to the WIP thread!&amp;#10;http://boardgamegeek.com/thread/1275178/wip-attack-omaha-beach-18-card-microgame-contest-e&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Here is the link to the 18 Card Microgame contest thread!&amp;#10;http://boardgamegeek.com/geeklist/178832/item/3575479#item3575479&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
